CHANGELOG — changelog.chg
========================

0.4.4 — 2026-03-12
  Fix 31: GetTileAt used ld de,level_map_cache which clobbered E (tile_x), making all tile lookups read 161 bytes past intended position — ground never detected, player fell through floor and crashed DrawSprite into attr/sysvar area.

0.4.3 — 2026-03-12
  Fix 28: DrawCharXY_Real jr nc->jr c — same inverted carry as Fix 27, latent crash for text drawn at screen row >=16.
  Fix 29: DrawSprite now masks before OR — (screen AND ~pixel) OR pixel — transparent background, no sprite data change needed.
  Fix 30: Replaced all three music tracks (SMB1 overworld/underground/title) with original compositions (D-major loop, A-minor phrase, C-major fanfare).

0.4.2 — 2026-03-12
  Fix 27: Inverted jr nc → jr c in DrawTile and DrawSprite screen row-advance; tiles in screen third 2 wrote second char-row to attribute/sysvar area causing crash.

0.4.1 — 2026-03-12
  Fixed illegal ld ixl/ixh,(hl) in UpdateEnemies — Z80 IX half-regs require register source, not memory indirect; routed via A.
  Fixed djnz .uen_loop out-of-range — loop body exceeds 127 bytes; replaced with dec b / jp nz.

0.4.0 — 2026-03-12
  Fix 26a: Added EI before RETI in HANDLER; DI zeros IFF2 so RETI alone never re-enables interrupts.
  Fix 26b: Changed keyboard scan from $BF (Enter row) to $7F (Space row $7FFE).
  Fix 26c: Rewrote enemy X as 16-bit in LoadEnemySpawns, UpdateEnemies, DrawEnemies, CheckEnemyPlayer.
  Fix 26d: Moved SP from $BF00 to $BBFE (free gap $841D–$BBFF); $BF00 let stack reach into MUSIC_OVERWORLD.

0.3.0 — 2026-03-11
  Fix 25a: Removed EI before RETI in interrupt handler (BC6E).
    RETI restores IFF1 from IFF2 automatically. The explicit EI opened a
    nested-interrupt window: handler could fire again while still executing,
    driving the stack down into BankSwitch/ClearScreen code each frame. This
    was the direct cause of the ShowLevelEntry infinite HALT loop.
  Fix 25b: Moved stack base from $BFF8 to $BF00.
    SP=$BFF8 with a 16-byte handler push + 6-byte Music_Tick push = SP reaches
    $BFE2, inside ClearScreen ($BFC5-$BFE5). Using freed turbo-loader space
    as the stack area (grows down from $BF00 into $BEFF, $BEFD...).
  Fix 25c: Swapped Setup_IM2 / ClearScreen order in GAME_START.
    ClearScreen fires EI. If IM2 isn't set up yet, any interrupt hits the IM0
    handler (garbage vector from data bus). Setup_IM2 now runs first.
  Fix 25d: Restored DoLevelBanking shim in bank2.
    InitLevel is in bank7. Calling BankSwitch directly from bank7 pages out
    bank7 instantly — the CPU then fetches the next instruction from level
    map data (which starts with $00/$01 = NOP/LD BC,nn). DoLevelBanking in
    bank2 safely performs the page-in, map copy, spawn copy, page-out sequence.
  Fix 25e: Added DS padding to W1L2_MAP.
    W1L2_MAP had 14 DEFB rows = 448 bytes. MAP_W*MAP_H = 704. Missing 256 bytes
    shifted W1L3_MAP 256 bytes early (C480 not C580), which shifted W1_SPAWNS
    to C740 instead of C840. LoadEnemySpawns reads from C840 — address mismatch.
    World 1 Level 2 loaded wrong map data; no enemies spawned on any level.
  Fix 25f: Corrected DS padding in all spawn slot tables (W1/W2/W3).
    Each spawn slot is 32 bytes. Padding was calculated as (32 - arbitrary),
    giving 42-byte slots that corrupted subsequent level reads.
    Correct padding = 32 - (entries×3 + 1) for each level.

0.2.0 — 2026-03-11
  Fix 24: Removed turbo loader ($BD00-$BDC6) from bank2.
  The turbo loader ORG $BD00 was assembling OVER SFX_Play (BD62) and
  SFX_Tick (BD7F), silently overwriting both routines with tape-loading
  code. Any sound effect trigger would have corrupted the machine.
  TURBO_ADDR EQU removed. Version string added to binary (MB128 v0.2.0).

0.1.4 — 2026-03-11
  Fix 23b: Pinned DrawCharXY trampoline to ORG $BFFD.

0.1.3 — 2026-03-11
  Fix 23a: Added DI/EI wrapper to ClearScreen.

0.1.2 — Previous session
  Fix 22: Space key row corrected to $7FFE.

0.1.1 — Previous session
  Fix 19: DoLevelBanking moved to bank2 (fixed).

0.1.0 — Previous session
  Initial working build.

0.5.0 — 2026-03-12
  Fix 32: DrawPlayer uses 16-bit sbc hl,de for screen_x instead of 8-bit (plr_x).
  Fix 33: GetTileAt now accepts HL=pixel_x (16-bit); pushes/pops BC to preserve caller B.
  Fix 34: Added CheckWalls routine; called from UpdatePlayer after applying vx.
  Fix 35: DrawEnemies djnz replaced with dec b / jp nz (loop body > 127 bytes).
  Fix 36: Removed redundant InitLevel call in mg_respawn (mg_level already calls it).
  Fix 37: IsSolid removed ld a,1/or a — A now preserved so CheckCeiling QBlock detection works.
  Fix 38: DrawPowerup uses 16-bit sbc hl,de for screen_x instead of 8-bit cam_x.
  Fix 39: QBlockHit and stomp score addition now propagate BCD carry to next byte.
  Fix 40: DrawHUD now shows 4 BCD score digits (score[1]:score[0]) instead of 2.

0.6.0 — 2026-03-12
  Fix 41: Hybrid ROM font — DrawCharXY_Real now uses ROM 1 ($3D00) for ASCII 32-127 and FONT_DATA for custom chars 128-255.
  Fix 41: GAME_START initialises BANKM sysvar ($5B5C) to $17 so BankSwitch preserves ROM 1 bit on every page.
  Fix 41: FONT_DATA ASCII 32-127 data deleted — 520 bytes freed from bank 2 ($8E00-$9007).

0.6.1 — 2026-03-13
  Fix 42a: CheckWalls right-probe jr z,.cw_done → jp z (target was +143 bytes, exceeds ±127 jr range).
  Fix 42b: CheckEnemyPlayer jr nz,.cep_no → jp nz (target was +128 bytes, exceeds ±127 jr range).

0.6.5 — 2026-03-14
  Fix 46: CheckWalls entry jr z,.cw_done → jp z — target $C7F3 is +144 bytes from $C761, exceeds ±127 jr range. Identical class of bug to Fix 42a at line 2386 in the same routine.

0.6.6 — 2026-03-14
  Fix 47: RenderLevel now skips call DrawTile entirely for AIR tiles (tile_id=0) using or a / jp z. Saves ~900 T-states per air cell per frame. W1L1 has ~120 air tiles visible per frame = ~108K T-states saved per frame loop (>50% reduction on typical screens).
  Fix 48: LoadEnemySpawns spawn Y now uses tile_y*16 - PLR_H instead of tile_y*16. Enemies spawned at tile_y=9 now have top-of-sprite at y=130 (feet at y=144 = top of ground row 9) instead of spawning body-deep inside the ground.

0.6.7 — 2026-03-14
  Fix 49: Added screen_y >= 177 clamp before every call DrawSprite in DrawPlayer, DrawEnemies, and DrawPowerup. screen_y >= 177 causes the 16th sprite row (y+15 = 192+) to map to $5800 (attr/sysvar area) via the Spectrum pixel address formula, corrupting memory and crashing to 48K BASIC with interrupts permanently disabled. Root cause: player/enemy Y not bounded before draw call; plr_y can reach 177-191 between a gravity step and the CheckGround snap on the next frame.

0.6.8 — 2026-03-14
  Fix 50: UpdateCamera missing push hl / push de at entry. The existing pop de / pop hl / ret at exit consumed UpdateCamera's own return address (into DE), UpdatePlayer's saved AF (into HL), then jumped to UpdatePlayer's saved BC as the program counter — a random address every frame. All crashes (display corruption, ROM1 execution, 48K BASIC reset, stuck AY note) traced back to this. Push order corrected: push hl / push de at entry matches pop de / pop hl at exit, restoring each register to its own saved value.

0.7.7 — 2026-03-14
  Fix 66: EraseSprite called with prev_sy=255 (Fix 62 sentinel) writes to $5Fxx (attr/sysvar area), corrupting BANKM at $5B5C and crashing to IM1 mode. Fix: skip EraseSprite in DrawPlayer and DrawEnemies when prev_sy==255. Added cp 255 / jr z guard before each EraseSprite call.
  Fix 67: Keyboard bit assignments wrong since Fix 55. Spectrum $DF row ($DFFE) layout is bit4=Y, bit3=U, bit2=I, bit1=O, bit0=P. Code was reading bit4 for P (actually Y) and bit3 for O (actually U). No O/P input ever registered. Fixed: bit 0,a for P (right) and bit 1,a for O (left). Space ($7F row bit0) was already correct.
